node.text:
I appreciate the pretty little cards that you took time to make for me, but know my little ones, you are my greatest gifts. I will always remember the first time I laid eyes on you and held you in my arms. That love and joy that swelled up in my heart, made me complete. Thank you for making me your mom and needing me always, through all those sleepless nights, tantrums and daily chaos. Thank you for showing me what it is to love selflessly and to give whole-heartedly. Thank you for constantly pushing my buttons and making me work on my patience.  Thank you for loving me despite my many shortcomings. In your eyes, I know I will always be perfect. Because of you, the simple moments in life are now more beautiful than before. 
Thank you for giving me a greater purpose in life. I’m blessed and forever grateful ❤️ #happymothersday

node.text:
2019, you have been nothing but awesome. Good and bad, we took things in stride because everything happens for a reason. Biggest milestone- having little Luke join our family! Thank you all for the love and positivity you gave here on this page.

Here’s wishing you and your loved ones a Happy New Year. To more adventures in 2020!

Love,
The Loks

node.text:
6 years old. Thank you for constantly bringing love, joy and laughter into our lives and being such sweet sisters to Luke. This year, the fairy may have taken all your front teeth but in our eyes you are still as adorable as ever. And tooth be told we love celebrating you. Happy Birthday, Leia Lauren ❤️❤️

Tutu Du Monde and Fendi outfits from @lm_bambini

node.text:
Great to see good sportsmanship here- to win and lose graciously. Proud of Leia for pushing through and Lauren for encouraging her sister even giving up her prize!

As to how they figured out the cube, there is a great 10min youtube tutorial by J Perm on the technique. Be warned, it's the longest 10min ever and I haven’t quite figured it out 😆

node.text:
A catchy tune to start the kids on their water saving journey! Luke is trying his best to too-too-taa-taa with his sisters 🤣
 
As they groove to Pinkfong, Water Wally and Sally, they’ll learn that turning off the🚰 water while brushing/soaping will go a long way in saving water.
 
To encourage water conservation, @pubsingapore is running a Turn Off The Tap Dance Challenge and 3 most energetic, creative and fun entries 💃🕺will dance away with $140 worth of Marina Square vouchers each!
 
To join, simply share a video via an IG post or IG story, of yourself, your child, or both, doing the dance. Hashtag #TurnOffTheTapDanceChallenge, tag @pubsingapore and encourage one friend to join the challenge. Remember to set your account to public.
 
Alternatively, send in your video via DM to PUB’s Instagram page. Contest ends 27 June. Good luck to all!
 
#TurnOffTheTapDanceChallenge #sp

node.text:
[GIVEAWAY] Making magic happen for Dad with delicate treats from @luna.singapore! We love how their range of artisan cakes and tarts are not only visually stunning but so yummy too!

Father’s Day is round the corner and we have 5 of their latest Goma Azuki cake (launched today) to giveaway! Bite into this light Goma sponge cake layered with Goma paste Chantilly and a smooth layer of Japanese Azuki red bean paste, wrapped in a modern, artful shell of velvet chocolate spray. 

To join, simply follow us and @luna.singapore, and tell us why Dad deserves a sweet treat 🍰
Giveaway for local residents only and closes 16 June. Winners can order their cake till end July. Good luck!
